  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "**FEATURE REQUEST**\r\n**Kubernetes version**: master (1.8.0alpha)\r\n\r\n**Proposal**\r\nSince the addition of chap authentication per volume the logical next feature would be the addition of a custom initiator name per persistent volume. This would allow for more fine grained configuration, and remove the need to configure the initiator name on the host (to be the same on all of them).\r\n\r\n**Idea**\r\nDefine a stable base interface to be used as a parent and clone it's settings to a new interface.\r\n\r\nThe new interfaces initiator can be set like that:\r\n\r\n```\r\niscsiadm -m iface -I iface_name --op=update -n  iface.initiatorname -v iqn.example.com\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux/5/html/Online_Storage_Reconfiguration_Guide/iscsioffload-softwareiscsi.html\r\n\r\n",
